00:29:21.600 --> 00:29:25.290
Michelle Obama-- none of these
people went to private school

00:29:25.290 --> 00:29:27.910
or grew up with a lot of money.

00:29:27.910 --> 00:29:30.100
They made themselves
into who they are.

00:29:30.100 --> 00:29:31.910
Now, than they did have luck.

00:29:31.910 --> 00:29:34.780
They had talent, for sure.

00:29:34.780 --> 00:29:37.480
But what to me is inspiring
about these stories

00:29:37.480 --> 00:29:39.130
is that they took
themselves further

00:29:39.130 --> 00:29:43.740
and they are avid about
continually learning.

00:29:43.740 --> 00:29:45.360
And that's certainly
true of Obama,

00:29:45.360 --> 00:29:47.810
whose story is especially
interesting when you think

00:29:47.810 --> 00:29:49.607
about how she has
managed the boundaries

00:29:49.607 --> 00:29:51.190
among the different
parts of her life,

00:29:51.190 --> 00:29:54.460
when she first moved
to the White House

00:29:54.460 --> 00:29:58.734
and how she created as close
to normal an environment

00:29:58.734 --> 00:30:00.400
for her kids, which
was super important,

00:30:00.400 --> 00:30:01.899
and how she's done
that and how they

00:30:01.899 --> 00:30:06.000
have done that as a family
is really quite instructive.

00:30:06.000 --> 00:30:11.070
Julie Foudy-- when she saw that
the men were getting a better

00:30:11.070 --> 00:30:15.910
deal than the women in
soccer, she stood up and said,

00:30:15.910 --> 00:30:18.037
that can't be.

00:30:18.037 --> 00:30:20.120
And she got the support
of people like Billie Jean

00:30:20.120 --> 00:30:23.100
King and others to
figure out a way

00:30:23.100 --> 00:30:27.250
to stand up to challenge
the status quo, based

00:30:27.250 --> 00:30:32.260
on her knowledge, really
cultivated by her parents,

00:30:32.260 --> 00:30:36.210
that you have to know what
really matters to yourself.

00:30:36.210 --> 00:30:38.210
Finally, Bruce, why
